data.text:
"Nikolay Zharkov" is a four-deck passenger motor ship of "Karelia" project and newest addition to the fleet on Russian River cruise market. On four decks on board “Nikolay Zharkov”, public spaces and living areas with staterooms will be perfectly divided for the convenience of guests. Modern laconic design, light atriums, elevator, comfortable staircases will give travelers a feeling of comfort and spaciousness. The ratio of passengers and crew members of the ship corresponds to the world level of Lux 2 to 1: for 176 guests there are 97 crew members. The ship will be launched and start its first navigation in 2025.

The ship will have an extensive navigation area which includes the Caspian Sea, the White Sea, and the Black Sea within 50 miles from ports, as well as inland waterways of Russia: the Volga-Baltic waterway, the White Sea-Baltic canal and the Volga-Don canal.
